[SetUp "1"]
[ChapterMode "gamebook"]

{ By move 26, Smyslov's advantage has increased to decisive proportions, so Liberzon decided to take desperate measures and sacrifice the knight on d5. What should White do now? Accept the knight, or play something else? }
26. Raf1 { White could have simply ignored the knight on d5 and continued with the siege of the f5 pawn. The knight would still be hanging in that case and Black would have been left with less counterplay with best play, although the position still remains complicated, of course.
Other moves that decline the sacrifice are also possible, but this one seems to be the most natural! White should be completely winning! } { [%csl Rf5][%cal Rf1f5,Rd4f5] } (26. cxd5? { But this recapture is probably a bit unnecessary as it provides Black with reasonable counterplay all of a sudden. }) 1-0


