due to Ng5-Nf4 ideas, so I decided to simplify stuff. } 23. Bxe6 { [%emt 1:02:00] } (23. Rxd8 Nxd8 { Felt like I am playing with fire as the knight goes back to
g5 at some point and Black has nice dark-square control on the kingside. }) 23... Rxd3 { [%emt 0:24:00] } 24. cxd3 { [%emt 1:02:00] This was the small point
of my "petite combinasion" as now the c3 pawn is immune. So I managed to
improve my structure and undouble the pawns in preparation for the rook
endgame. } 24... Kxe6 { [%emt 0:16:00] } (24... fxe6 { Although even in the game there are f5 pushes soo } 25. Kd2 { I guess the verdict is close to being equal. }) 25. Kd2 { [%emt 1:02:00]
Here I agreed to a draw as I was tired, unsure if I have anything and worried
I might even lose a position like this. Initially I wrote it was the correct
decision, as at the moment I did this the team was doing very well, but
ultimately we went on to draw this highly important match. I think it would
have been very beneficial for me to try and play this endgame, although with
tiredness and lack of concentration who knows what would have happened.
Although my older opponent also must have been not at the best. } 1/2-1/2


