structure and target the f2 pawn. } 21. g3 { [%emt 1:10:00] Here I was somewhat
reconciled with a draw - and probably too little upset with it because I did
manage to catch my opponent and get a good position out of the opening. } (21. h4 { WAs the alternative I considered, but after } 21... Rg8 22. g4 Rh8 { I thought was
just dead equal - not a good version of Zirk's g4-h4 stuff. // Stockfish
indeed confirms that arguably only Black can talk about being better. }) (21. Kb2 h4 { When the g-pawn is
kinda target (although I guess I can move it). // Engine agrees with this
assessment. }) 21... h4 { [%emt 0:24:00] } 22. g4 { [%emt 1:04:00] I really didn't
want to open up the h-file and allow the rook in. } (22. Kb2 hxg3 23. hxg3 Rh2 { I also thought was kinda equal, but somewhat annoying with the rook on the 2nd
rank. // For the engine it probably doesn't matter, but as a human I really
don't want ot allow the rampaging rook. }) 22... Rd8 { [%emt 0:24:00] Finally
this exchanging mechanism. Here I was worried my kingside might become weak
due to Ng5-Nf4 ideas, so I decided to simplify stuff. } 23. Bxe6 { [%emt 1:02:00] } (23. Rxd8 Nxd8 { Felt like I am playing with fire as the knight goes back to
g5 at some point and Black has nice dark-square control on the kingside. //
Tbh, here I overestimated the danger a bit - this is just an equal endgame, e.
g. } 24. Kb2 Ne6 25. c4 Ng5 26. Be4 { And this Ng5 didn't achieve much - we
don't fear the exchange on e4 somehow. Stockfish. }) 23... Rxd3 { [%emt 0:24:00] } 24. cxd3 { [%emt 1:02:00] This was the small point of my "petite combinasion"
as now the c3 pawn is immune. So I managed to improve my structure and
undouble the pawns in preparation for the rook endgame. } 24... Kxe6 { [%emt 0:16:00] } (24... fxe6 { Although
even in the game there are f5 pushes soo } 25. Kd2 { I guess the verdict is
close to being equal. } 25... a5 { But this is an important move, to prevent some play
along the a-file. } (25... Kf7 26. b4 { Is also fine tho - how am I getting to
the queenside after a6? But I guess gaining space is better. } 26... a6)) (24... Rxc3+ 25. Kd2 { Ofc loses for Black. }) 25. Kd2 { [%emt 1:02:00] Here I agreed to a
draw as I was tired, unsure if I have anything and worried I might even lose a
position like this. Initially I wrote it was the correct decision, as at the
moment I did this the team was doing very well, but ultimately we went on to
draw this highly important match. I think it would have been very beneficial
for me to try and play this endgame, although with tiredness and lack of
concentration who knows what would have happened. Although my older opponent
also must have been not at the best. // To be completely fair, if anyone is on
the better side of things it is White, although I thought after the f-pawn
pushes there is nothing bad for Black apparent. It might indeed be so, e.g. } 25... f5 (25... a5 { Is also more than fine for equality, tho. }) 26. b4 fxg4 27. fxg4 f5 { There are easier ways, according to Stocfkish, but I thought this direct
option is the simplest. } 28. gxf5+ Kxf5 29. Rf1+ Ke6 30. Rg1 { With that being
said, White does have some pressure here. In any case - especially after my
opponent took with the king on e6 I could have stopped, calculated and maybe
considered playing on - as I objectively shouldn't be risking that much unless
I get braindead somehow by Miracle. // In any case, a not very eventful but a
very instructive game from which I can learn a lot and draw the following
lessons/conclusions:  - I really need a normal, sharp and open variation
against the Sicilian ASAP - I should prepare a bit better for the games. It is
true that it is tricky with two games a day and multiple possible opponents,
but here I was just a bit lazy.  - More broadly, some variations in my
repertoire could benefit from knowing more plans and ideas instead of being 15
moves of theory and then blank (signs of Chessable generation). - I should get
better at handling positions where I have some pressure/positional advantage 
(maybe some bishop vs knight with/without rooks endgames) or some games by
some player like Karpov. - I should really start calculating in my games more
- even when tired. } 1/2-1/2


