{ Indic has managed to outplay his opponent and obtain a winning endgame. But
here, under severe time pressure, he falters. }
56... Rxa4?? { [%emt 0:00:03] A
blunder that allows White to come very close to a draw. } (56... Rb3 { It was
important to defend the b6 pawn as then it is also not easy to get to the g6
pawn, e.g. } 57. Nd7 (57. Rg7 Kf6) 57... Nd2+ 58. Kg2 Nc4 { And Black retains a
decisive advantage. }) 57. Rxb6 { [%emt 0:00:03] } 57... Kf5 { [%emt 0:00:03] The final
mistake, giving up the g6 pawn and all hopes of success. } (57... Nd2+ { Would
have retained some chances: } 58. Kf2 (58. Ke2 Re4+ 59. Kxd2 Rxe5 60. Rxa6 Kf5 { Is a won endgame for Black - the king is cut off. }) 58... Rf4+ 59. Kg2 Rf6 { Preserving the two pawns. In time trouble, anything can happen - but I suspect
Black would have good winning chances in practice. }) 58. Nxg6 { [%emt 0:00:02]
And now with only a-pawn left - Black can't win and the game ended in a draw.
One of those games that ended up costing us the playoff stage! } 1/2-1/2


