{ In a close-fought and topsy turvy game, Indjic has managed to outplay Alice
and obtained a winning position with a clean extra exchange. }
37. Rda2 { [%emt 0:01:07] A bit unecessary - why give up the d3 pawn? } (37. Ra7 { Attacking the bishop on e7 and keeping everything under control, is quite
clean, e.g. } 37... Bg5 38. Rda2 Qxd3 39. Rd7 Qg6 40. Raa7 { And Rh7 will be deadly
eventually. }) 37... Qxd3 { [%emt 0:00:50] } 38. Rd2?? { [%emt 0:00:29] But this
is a serious blunder. Indjic was probably hoping to invate along the d-file,
but now he is met with a nasty surprise. } (38. Qf1 { would keep
the advantage, as now } 38... Qg6 39. Bd5 { The rook on a6 is defended and White keeps
control. } 39... Qh5 40. Bxf3 gxf3 { There is no mate and White is just material up. }) 38... Qg6 { [%emt 0:00:17] A nasty surprise, threatening the deadly Qh5. White
has to give up some material now. } 39. Bd5? { [%emt 0:00:43] } (39. Bxg4 { Was a slightly better version, although White is lost all the same. }) 39... Qxa6 { [%emt 0:00:03] } 40. Bxf3 { [%emt 0:00:01] } 40... gxf3 { [%emt 0:00:03] And now
Black is completely winning with a clean extra piece, although by some miracle
Indjic escaped with a draw. You could say he was lucky to do so, but
considering the position he had before... Some games cost more than
half-a-point. } 1/2-1/2


