[Black "Wei, Yi"]
[Result "1-0"]
[WhiteElo "2389"]
[WhiteTeam "Indonesia"]
[BlackElo "2722"]
[BlackTeam "China"]
[Annotator "mistr"]
[Variant "From Position"]
[ECO "?"]
[Opening "?"]
[StudyName "Croatia Bulldogs - Shangai Tigers, PCL Week 4 2023 - Highlights"]
[ChapterName "Sukandar, Irine Kharisma - Wei, Yi"]
[ChapterURL "https://lichess.org/study/IOe15xP6/xZvjnEKD"]
[FEN "1q1r2k1/pb3p2/1pB2n2/4b2r/2PN2p1/P2PQ3/2N2PP1/1R2RK2 b - - 0 29"]
[SetUp "1"]

{ One of the reasons why the first
round of the match was so sucessful for us was the debut game of Irene
Sukandar, who managed to score one of the most major upsets in the Pro Chess
League by beating the Chinese heavyweight Wei Yi. To be completely fair, she
was very much outplayed by Wei Yi, who obtained a dominating position with
real attacking chances on the White king. However, in severe time trouble, he
missed the best way to clinch the game - and on move 29, his task was already
much more difficult - although still possible! } { [%evp 0,75,29,13,37,51,95,73,64,69,60,49,38,38,43,9,22,12,6,10,20,10,28,12,11,
-3,0,-1,0,-8,8,30,37,-10,24,12,-43,-68,-68,-83,-117,-96,-110,-118,-31,-238,-43,
-81,28,-65,-70,-70,-87,-97,17,-72,0,0,-54,-52,213,76,76,87,91,91,109,116,111,
108,114,119,656,631,822,882,29997,29998] }
29... Kg7? { This is a
natural move to make in the time trouble - but it turns out to be a bad
mistake as the king will actually be somewhat exposed here. But more
importantly - White obtains a whole tempo, which is a big luxury in a position
such as this one. } (29... Qd6 { attacking the d4 knight. }) (29... Ba6 { Removing the bishop
from the attack. }) (29... g3 { Trying to open up the king (although this last
one is particularly messy and unclear). }) 30. Rb5 { A remarkable
move, attacking the bishop on e5 and pinning it to the rook. Official
commentators mentioned this move is impossible to find, but Irene found it
very quickly - and suddenly White is completely winning. } { [%cal Rb5h5] } 30... Bf4 31. Qe7 { Now we see the drawback of having the king on g7 - Ne6 is one of the
ideas. } { [%cal Gd4e6] } 31... Rh1+ 32. Ke2 Rxe1+ 33. Kxe1 Bxc6 34. Ne6+ Kg6 35. Nxd8 Bxb5 36. Qxf7+ { Much stronger than taking the bishop. White has a nice tactical, mating finish
available. } 36... Kf5 37. Nd4+ Kg5 38. N8e6+ { And Wei Yi resigned here as the mate
happens on f5 on the next move. A remarkable game and one of the biggest
upsets in the PCL history! } 1-0


