[SetUp "1"]

{ Bardiya Daneshvar has been playing some tremendous chess in the ongoing Pro
Chess League. In the opening game of the round, he came close to getting
another massive scalp, as he obtained a completely won position against the
French nr. 1 player Maxime Vachier Lagrave. }
32. Bxg6 { [%emt 0:00:16] A fully
correct "sacrifice", opening up the 7th rank. } 32... Rf8 { [%emt 0:00:23] The only
way to stay in the game. } (32... fxg6 33. Rb7 { Immediately loses. }) 33. Rb7 { This would have clinched the game, as f7 pawn now can't be defended. } (33. Rb8 { [%emt 0:00:07] Was played in the game instead. Potentially it is even a
mouseslip. White is not worse even after the piece blunder, but instead
Bardiya could have ended the game on the spot. }) 0-1


