[SetUp "1"]

{ This game featured a very sharp and tactical Najdorf that led to this ultra
complicated position. White needs to be very careful as the cloud storms are
gathering over the kingside. }
22. Qg1?? { [%emt 0:00:48] This is a big blunder
as it allows the opponent to open up the f-file. } (22. gxh7+ { Was absolutely
necessary, when after } 22... Kh8 23. Qg1 { The position is razor sharp - but
completely unclear! Note that } 23... Ra8 24. Rxd5 { Doesn't win a piece for Black! }) 22... fxg6 { [%emt 0:00:01] Now it is all over as Nf2 is
unavoidable. } { [%cal Gg4f2] } 23. Rxd5 { [%emt 0:00:45] } 23... Rxf1 { [%emt 0:00:06] } 24. Bxf1 { [%emt 0:00:00] } 24... Nf2+ { [%emt 0:00:01] } 25. Qxf2 { [%emt 0:00:01] } 25... Qxf2 { [%emt 0:
00:00] And Josefine had no problems with converting her advantage, giving the
Bears a glimmer of hope in the final round! } 0-1


