[SetUp "1"]

{ In this complex and strange-looking position, White is struggling to find a
convincing compensation for the pawn. Polina decided to grab the pawn on c3,
but it turned out to be a decisive mistake. }
25. Rxc3 { [%emt 0:01:24] } (25. Qe3 { A move like this, adding some control over the e5 square, was necessary, but
it is not easy for a human to put the queen on the same file where the rook on
e8 is resiidng. }) (25. Ne5 { Was also probably safer than what happened in the
game, although after } 25... Be4 26. Qe2 Bxb1 27. Rxb1 Nd5 { White's initiative is
dwindling and Polina would have to face an uphill struggle for a draw here. }) 25... e5 { [%emt 0:00:30] A simple move, threatening a deadly
fork on e4. White was forced to give up a piece for not much compensation, and
Robson had no trouble converting the game and scoring a point for the Unicorns. } { [%cal Re5d4,Ge5e4] } 0-1


