[Black "Daneshvar, Bardiya"]
[Result "0-1"]
[WhiteElo "2702"]
[BlackElo "2510"]
[TimeControl "300+2"]
[Annotator "USER"]
[Variant "From Position"]
[ECO "?"]
[Opening "?"]
[StudyName "Croatia Bulldogs - California Unicorns, Pro Chess League 2023, Week 1 Highlights"]
[ChapterName "Robson, Ray - Daneshvar, Bardiya"]
[ChapterURL "https://lichess.org/study/agqbHg2f/tFfjeQVZ"]
[FEN "6k1/4rp2/2Bp2pb/1p3n2/1P3P1p/3R3P/1r1B2P1/3R2K1 b - - 0 45"]
[SetUp "1"]

{ This game featured a crazy battle in the Accelerated Dragon in which White
was clearly better at some point. But at some point, he lost all the advantage
and by move 45, Black managed to take over in Robson's severe time trouble.
This is where the culmination of the game happened. }
45... Rxd2 { [%emt 0:00:11]
This exchange sacrifice is actually not fully correct, but it is very
practical and tricky to handle as White's dark-squared bishop is now gone. } (45... Rc7 { The engine says that Black is clearly winning after a move like
this, trying to get the rook to c2. }) 46. R3xd2 { [%emt 0:00:01] } 46... Bxf4 { [%emt 0:
00:01] } 47. Ra2 { [%emt 0:00:01] } 47... Nd4 { [%emt 0:00:06] The knight
and bishop are creating some nasty tactical threats and it is very difficult
to keep track of them with just seconds on the clock. } { [%csl Gd4,Gf4] } 48. Bd5?! { [%emt 0:00:
03] } (48. Rxd4 Be3+ 49. Kf1 Bxd4 { Would have actually lead to a drawn endgame,
but it is not so easy to evaluate this in time trouble. }) 48... Ne2+ { [%emt 0:
00:02] } 49. Kh1?? { [%emt 0:00:03] But this is the crucial mistake in time
trouble as the king will be prone to various mating threats in the corner. } (49. Kf1 { Was necessary, when Black would have to go for something like } 49... Ng3+ 50. Kf2 Kg7 { With definite compensation for the exchange - but White is still
in the game. }) 49... Nc3 { [%emt 0:00:08] Now it is all
over as everything is hanging in White's position and he has to lose material
due to the back rank issues. } { [%cal Rc3d5,Rc3d1,Rc3a2] } 50. Ra8+ { [%emt 0:00:02] } 50... Kg7 { [%emt 0:00:00] } 51. g3 { [%emt 0:00:01] } (51. Rd3 Re1# { Is mate - this is why it was wrong to
go to the corner with the king. }) (51. Rf1 Nxd5 { Loses a piece. }) 51... Nxd1 { [%emt 0:00:05] And Black is now completely winning! } 0-1


