[FEN "5k2/1b3pp1/4p3/3nP3/3PB3/1P4KP/p1N2P2/8 b - - 0 40"]
[SetUp "1"]

{ The following game featured one of the most remarkable and stunning blunders
I have ever seen in online chess. One I still can't believe actually happened.
Deac has managed to completely outplay the opponent and he is just about to
finish him off with a nice knight diversion. }
40... Nb4 { [%emt 0:00:01] Ensuring a win of the piece or the promotion of a pawn. } { [%cal Rb4c2,Ga2a1,Rb7e4] } 41. Nxb4 { [%emt 0:00:06] This is equivalent to resignation and I am shocked that
Swiercz decided to play on in this position. Alas, by some miracle, it
actually worked as Deac probably didn't expect this move at all. } 41... Bxe4?? { [%emt 0:00:01] I still can't believe this move was played. I am not sure if
Deac thought this was a check, if he missed whether the pawn on a2 is on the
attack or if he just premoved, expecting White to go with the knight to a1. He
had 9 seconds on the clock at this moment when this fateful mistake happened. } 42. Nxa2 { [%emt 0:00:01] The biggest tragedy here is that White now has a
completely won endgame due to the passed b-pawn. Absolutely incredible. } 1-0


