[SetUp "1"]

{ This endgame is dead equal, but here Bardiya decided to try and go for the
win. }
37... Rg8 { [%emt 0:00:07] Trying to get in some g5 play, but this allows
White to open up the queenside. } (37... Rd7) (37... Rd6) (37... Ra8 { Also wouldn''t lose as it
prevents the b5 pawn push: } 38. b5 axb5+ 39. Kxb5 Ra3 { And suddenly White has
to be a bit careful. }) 38. b5 { [%emt 0:00:26] } 38... axb5 { [%emt 0:00:06] } 39. Kxb5 { [%emt 0:00:00] } 39... g5 { [%emt 0:01:06] } 40. Rc6 { [%emt 0:00:06] And now White is
significantly better. } 40... gxh4 (40... f4 { Was the only way to stay in the game,
after } 41. exf4 (41. gxf4 g4) 41... gxh4 42. gxh4 Rf8 { Black has some
drawing chances. But given that a draw would have been tantamount to a loss
for the team, it ultimately doesn't matter that much. }) 41. gxh4 { And now White is winning as he is too active and Meier went on to
clinch the match for the Unicorns. } { [%cal Rc6e6,Gc5d6] } 1-0


