1. e4 e6 2. d4 d5 3. Nc3 Nf6 { The Classical Variation is a variation of the French Defence against the 3.Nc3 move-order, characterized by the development of the knight to f6. The knight puts pressure on the e4 pawn and prompts White to do something about it. } { [%cal Rf6e4] } *


