better to go with this bishop move and pressure the f3 knight before jumping
to f5. } 21. Ne5 Nf5 { And here, due to the pressure on the
d4 pawn, White doesn't have time for the Bb1 maneuver due to } { [%cal Rf5d4,Rd8d4] } 22. Bb1 (22. Qe1 { As now the d4 pawn is immune due to
the threat of the knight sacrifice on f7 } { [%cal Re5f7,Re1e6,Ra2e6] } 22... Nxd4 23. Nxf7 Kxf7 24. Rxd4 { And
Black can't recapture on d4 due to mate: } 24... Rxd4 25. Qxe6+ Kf8 26. Qf7#) 22... Rxd4) 21. g4 { This is not at all that bad due to very concrete reasons,
although it does look a bit risky/strange to weaken the king's shelter this
