is not so easy to judge that the knight on c5 will not be that strong after } 22. Nc5 { It looks as if Bxd6 and Nxb7 is a massive threat,
but Black can calmly defend with } { [%csl Gb4,Rb7,Gc5] } 22... Bc8 { And nothing
terrible is apparent for now. The position remains roughly equal. } { [%csl Gb7][%cal Gc8b7] }) 22. a6 { A good undermining move, threatening both axb7 and Nxc6
and virtually forcing Black to give up the bishop pair. } { [%csl Rc6][%cal Ra6b7] } 22... Bxd3 { This move diverts the knight form b4 and gives Black time to play b6
without losing the c6 pawn. This is virtually the only move that doesn't lose
