quite work as after } 25... c5 26. dxc5 bxc5 { It transpries that the rook can be very
active on the queenside, e.g. after } 27. Ra5 { This rook inclusion is one of
the main reasons why it was more flexible to start with the push of the g-pawn
or the h-pawn. }) 25... Rd7?? { Alas, Zukertort doesn't exploit
the inacuraccy, but instead makes a fatal - and a fairly simple blunder,
