1. e4 e6 2. d4 d5 3. Nc3 (3. exd5) 3... Bb4 4. exd5 exd5 5. Bd3 { [%cal Gd3h7] } 5... Nc6 6. Ne2 { [%cal Gc3e2] } (6. Nf3 Bg4 { [%csl Gf3][%cal Gc3e2,Gc1f4,Gf4d6,Gf3h4,Gf3g6] }) 6... Nge7 { [%csl Gf6][%cal Gg8e7,Gc8f5,Gc1g5,Gf7f6] } 7. O-O Bf5! { "Alekhine immediately challenges the White KB. Black now has at least an
equal game. Capablanca plays listlessly for the next few moves allowing
Alekhine to get a positional advantage." (Taulbut 83) } { [%cal Gc8f5] } (7... Bg4!? { (Grunfeld) }) 8. Bxf5 { [%cal Ge7f5] } (8. Bg5 Qd7 9. a3 Bxc3 10. Nxc3 Bg6 11. Qd2 Nf5 $10 { Steiner-Colle 1927 }) (8. Ng3 $10 { (Euwe 76) } 8... Bg6 (8... Nxd4 9. Bxf5 Ndxf5 (9... Bxc3? 10. Bh3 $16) 10. Nxf5 Nxf5 (10... Bxc3? 11. Nxe7 $18) 11. Nxd5 $16 { Becker }) 9. Nce2 (9. f4 f5) 9... Qd7 10. Nf4 Bd6 11. c3 Nd8 $10 { Maroczy-Nagy 1928 }) (8. a3 { [%csl Gb4] } 8... Bxc3 9. bxc3 Qd7 $10 { (Schwarz 67) }) 8... Nxf5 { [%cal Ge7f5] } 9. Qd3 Qd7 { [%csl Gf4][%cal Gc1f4,Gc1d2] } (9... Bxc3? 10. Nxc3 Nfxd4 11. Re1+ Ne6 12. Nxd5 $16 { (Schwarz 67) }) 10. Nd1?! { "This plan of
exchanging off Black's well placed knight on f5 costs White valuable time."
(Taulbut 83) } { [%csl Gf5][%cal Gd1e3,Gc2c3] } (10. Nb5 Bd6 (10... Ba5 { [%cal Gb4a5,Ga5b6] } 11. Bf4 Nb4! 12. Qh3 Ne7 13. Qxd7+ Kxd7 $10 { (eco 74/81) } 14. Na3 Rae8 15. Ng3 g6 16. Rad1 Na6 17. Nb5 Nc8 18. c3 c6 { Bernstein-Guimard Groningen 1946 }) 11. Bf4 O-O 12. Nxd6 Nxd6 13. Rfe1 $10 { (eco 74/81) } 13... Rae8 14. Ng3 g6 15. c3 Nd8 $10 { Poliak-Bondarevsky USSR 1946 }) (10. Bf4 O-O-O $10 { (Alekhine) } { [%csl Gb4][%cal Gg7g5,Gc3b5,Ga2a3,Gb4d6,Gf4d6] } 11. Nb5 { [%cal Ga2a4,Gb2b4,Ga5b6,Gb6f2] } 11... Bd6) (10. Bd2 { [%cal Gb4d6,Gd6h2] }) 10... O-O (10... O-O-O) 11. Ne3? (11. Bf4 Rfe8 12. c3 Bd6 13. Bxd6 Qxd6 14. Ne3 $10 { Lilienthal-Koltanowsky Sitges 1934 }) 11... Nxe3 12. Bxe3 { "White's minor pieces are now obstructing the vital King's file.
This is a convincing proof of the inexactitude of his opening strategy."
(Alekhine) } 12... Rfe8 $15 { (Pachman 68) } { [%csl Ge3,Gd5,Gc7,Gb7,Ga7,Gf7,Gg7,Gh7][%cal Ge3f4] } (12... Bd6 13. c3 Ne7 $10 { (Fine 48) }) 13. Nf4? (13. c3 { [%cal Ge2g3] } 13... Bd6 14. Bf4 Bxf4 15. Nxf4 Re4 $15 { (Taulbut 83) }) (13. Ng3 $10 { (Euwe 76) }) (13. Bf4 $10 { (Alekhine) } 13... Re4 14. c3 Bd6 15. Bxd6 Qxd6 16. Ng3 $10) 13... Bd6! $15 { (Schwarz 67, eco 74/81) } { [%csl Ge3,Gd5][%cal Gc2c3,Gd6f4,Gd1d3] } (13... Ne7 { [%csl Gf4][%cal Gf4h5] }) 14. Rfe1?! (14. c3!? { (Alekhine) } { [%csl Ge4] } 14... Ne7 (14... Re4 { [%csl Gf4] } 15. Ne2 { [%csl Ge2] } 15... Rae8 { [%csl Gd5][%cal Gd3b5,Gb7b6] } 16. Qb5 { [%csl Gh2][%cal Gh3h2] } (16. Ng3 { [%csl Gg3] } 16... Bxg3 17. hxg3 Ne7 { [%csl Ge3,Gc4] } 18. Rfe1 Nf5 $15 { (Levenfish) }) 16... b6 17. Qxd5 Bxh2+ 18. Kxh2 Qxd5)) (14. Nxd5?! Bxh2+ 15. Kxh2 Qxd5 { [%cal Gc5e5] } 16. c3 (16. c4 Ne5? (16... Qh5+ 17. Kg1 Rad8 { [%cal Gc6e5] } 18. d5 (18. Qc3 { [%cal Ge8e4] } 18... Re4 { [%cal Ge4h4,Gc6d4] }) (18. Rfe1 Ne5 (18... h6) 19. Qb3 Ng4 20. Bf4 { [%csl Gd4,Gb7,Gc7] } 20... Rxe1+ 21. Rxe1 g5 22. Bxc7 Rxd4 23. Re8+ Kg7) 18... Qc3 (18... Rd6 $17 { (Alekhine) } { [%cal Gc6e5,Ge5g4] }) (18... Ne5 { [%cal Gd3d1] }) 19. Ne5 Rfd1 20. Rg6 $17 { PS }) 17. Qf5) 16... Ne5 { [%cal Gd3f5] } 17. Qf5 g6 18. Qh3 Nc4 { [%csl Gc4,Ge3] }) 14... Nb4 { [%csl Gc3,Gc2][%cal Gb4d3] } 15. Qb3?! (15. Qd2 { [%csl Gd2,Gf4][%cal Gd2f4] } 15... Qf5 16. Rec1 { [%csl Gb4,Ge8][%cal Ge8e4] } 16... h5! $15 { (Alekhine) } (16... Re4 { [%cal Gf4e2] } 17. Ne2 $15 { Becker } { [%csl Gg3] } 17... Rae8 18. c3 Nc6) (16... c6 17. c3 (17. Ne2) 17... Na6 { [%csl Gf4] }) (16... Bxf4 17. Bxf4 Nc6 (17... c6 { [%csl Gb5] } 18. Qxb4 Qxf4 19. Qxb7 Qxd4))) 15... Qf5 { -/+ (Euwe 38) =/+
(Fine 48) } { [%csl Gf4][%cal Gb3b4] } 16. Rac1? (16. Re2 { [%cal Ge2c2] } 16... Bxf4 17. Qxb4 Qh5 { (Tartakover/du Mont) } (17... Bxh2+ { [%cal Gf5h5,Gh5e2] })) (16. Rec1 { [%csl Gc2][%cal Ge8e1] } 16... Bxf4 (16... a5! { [%cal Gf4e2] } 17. a3 { [%cal Ga5a4] } (17. a4 { [%csl Gb4] } 17... Bxf4 { [%csl Gf4] }) (17. Ne2 Bxh2+ 18. Kxh2 Qh5+ 19. Kg1 Qxe2) 17... a4 18. Qc3 Nc6 { [%csl Ga5,Gc4,Ga4][%cal Ga4b2,Gf4d3,Ge8e4,Ge6e5] } 19. Ne2? (19. Nd3 Na5 { [%cal Ga5c4] } (19... Re6 $17 { [%cal Ga8e8] }) 20. b3 { [%csl Gd4][%cal Ga5c4,Ga8a3] } 20... b5 { [%cal Gd3b4] }) 19... Bxh2+) 17. Bxf4 (17. Qxb4 { [%csl Ge3,Gc6][%cal Gc6e7,Gc6b4] } 17... Rxe3 18. fxe3 Bxe3+ 19. Kh1 Bxc1 20. Rxc1 Re8 21. Qxb7 Qxc2 { (Tartakover/du Mont) }) 17... Qxf4 18. Qxb4 Re2 $17 { Becker }) (16. Nd3 Nxd3 17. Qxd3 Qxd3 18. cxd3 { = (Capablanca) } { [%cal Ga8a6,Ga6c6,Gc6c2,Gc2b2] } 18... Bb4 (18... a5 19. a4 Ra6) 19. Rec1 c6 $17 { /\a5! (Alekhine) } (19... a3 20. Ba5 { Tartakover })) 16... Nxc2! { [%csl Gc2] } 17. Rxc2 { [%cal Gf5f4] } (17. Qxc2 Qxc2 18. Rxc2 Bxf4 19. Bxf4 Rxe1#) 17... Bxf4? (17... Qxf4 { "This is the possibility
overlooked by Capablanca at his 16th move."  (Alekhine) } { [%csl Gh2][%cal Gc2c5,Gg2g3] } 18. g3 { [%csl Gb7][%cal Gf4h2,Gb3d5] } (18. Bxf4 Rxe1# { [%cal Ge1g1] }) (18. Qxb7 Qxh2+ 19. Kf1 c6 (19... Qh1+ 20. Ke2 Qxg2)) 18... Qf3!? (18... Qf5 $17 { (Euwe 76) } 19. Rce2 { [%cal Ge1e2] } (19. Qxb7 Qxc2) 19... b6 (19... Rab8 { [%csl Gb8] }) 20. Qb5 h5 { "This pawn prepares to advance to h3 where it can form a mating
