1. e4 { After Caruana lost game 1 of tiebreaker it makes sense to go for a win, also e4 was probably only move prepared for the match. } 1... c5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 e5 6. Ndb5 d6 7. Nd5 Nxd5 8. exd5 Ne7 { Continuing with the variation he played in game 12. Caruana had a rest day to look up the variation. } (8... Nb8) 9. c4 Ng6 (9... a6 { Would lose instantly. } { [%cal Ge7b8,Gf8d6] } 10. Qa4 { [%csl Gd6] } 10... Bd7 (10... Qd7 11. Nxd6+ (11. Nc7+) 11... Kd8 12. Nxf7+) (10... axb5 11. Qxa8) 11. Nxd6#) 10. Qa4 Bd7 { [%cal Gf8d6] } 11. Qb4 { [%csl Gd6,Gb7][%cal Gb4b7] } 11... Qb8 { Although this move can look a bit weird, b8 square is common place for queen in Sicilian. } { [%csl Gb7][%cal Gb8d6,Ga7a6] } (11... Bf5 { Was played in the 12th game } 12. h4 h5) 12. h4 h5 { [%cal Gh4h5] } (12... Be7 13. h5 { [%cal Gg6f4] } 13... Nf8 (13... Nf4 14. Bxf4) 14. h6 g6 $16 { White would have an advantage. }) 13. Be3 { [%csl Ga7] } 13... a6 14. Nc3 a5 15. Qb3 { [%csl Gc2,Gd1][%cal Gb3d1] } (15. Qa3 { Was also possible with an idea of putting pressure on d6 pawn. } { [%cal Ga3d6,Gb2b4,Ga3b2] }) 15... a4 { [%csl Ga4] } 16. Qd1 Be7 { [%csl Gh4][%cal Ge7h4] } 17. g3 { [%csl Gh5] } 17... Qc8 { [%csl Gc8,Gb8][%cal Gd7g4] } (17... O-O 18. Qxh5) 18. Be2 Bg4 19. Rc1 { [%cal Gc1c5,Gc4c5] } (19. Bxg4 hxg4 (19... Qxg4 20. Qxg4 hxg4 21. Ke2 { [%cal Gh4h5] } 21... f5 22. h5 Nf8 23. b3 axb3 24. axb3 { [%cal Gf5f4,Gg7g5] } 24... Rxa1 25. Rxa1 Rxh5 { [%csl Ge7,Gf8][%cal Gc3b5,Ga1a7] }) 20. c5 dxc5 21. h5 Nf8 22. h6 { Was a better option for white. } { [%csl Gg4,Gf8,Ge7,Ge8] }) 19... Bxe2 20. Qxe2 Qf5 { White could have prepared c5 idea, before playing it. } { [%cal Ge5e4] } 21. c5 { c5 is common motive in this type of positions. White is happy to sacrifice c-pawn for getting passed d-pawn. } (21. Nb5 { [%cal Gc1c7] } 21... O-O 22. O-O Rfc8 23. Rfd1 Nf8 24. c5 $16) 21... O-O { White is in an awkward place now. Black threatens to take on c5. } { [%cal Gd6c5] } (21... dxc5 22. Bxc5 Bxc5 23. Qb5+ { [%csl Gc5][%cal Gb5e8] } 23... Qd7 24. Qxc5 $16 { White's pieces are better placed. White would be better. } { [%csl Gd7,Gf5][%cal Gc5f8] }) 22. c6 { [%csl Gc6,Gd5][%cal Gc3d5] } (22. cxd6 Bxd6 23. O-O (23. Nb5 Bb4+) 23... Nf4 (23... e4 24. Bd4 { [%cal Gg6e5] } 24... Rfe8 { [%cal Ge8e4] }) 24. Qf3 (24. gxf4 exf4 { [%cal Gf4f3] } 25. Qf3 { [%cal Gf3f5] } (25. Bd4 f3 26. Qe4 Qh3 $19) 25... Qg6+ 26. Kh1 fxe3 { And Black is fine }) 24... Qg6 $15) 22... bxc6 23. dxc6 { White has passed c-pawn but black got full control of center and he can control c-pawn relatively easy. } 23... Rfc8 { [%cal Gc8c6] } 24. Qc4 { [%cal Ge2c4] } (24. Nd5 Qe4 { [%csl Gd5][%cal Ge4h1] } 25. Nxe7+ Nxe7 26. O-O Rxc6) 24... Bd8 { [%cal Gd8a5] } (24... Ra5 25. Nd5 (25. O-O Qe6 { [%cal Gc3d5] }) 25... Qf3) (24... Qe6 25. Nd5) 25. Nd5 e4 { Great play by magnus } { [%cal Gg6e5,Ge5d3,Ge5f3] } (25... Ba5+ 26. Kf1 { [%csl Gh2][%cal Gf1g1] } 26... e4) 26. c7?? { Unfortunate blunder that decided game instantly. } (26. Bd4 { [%cal Gg6e5] } 26... Ba5+ { [%cal Gf5f3] } 27. Bc3 Bxc3+ 28. Rxc3 Ra5 29. Ne3 Qe5) 26... Bxc7 27. Nxc7 Ne5 { [%cal Ge5c4] } 28. Nd5 (28. Qd5 { [%cal Gf5d5] } 28... Rxc7 (28... Rab8 { [%cal Gc8c7] } 29. O-O Rxc7 30. Qxd6 (30. Rxc7 Nf3+ { [%cal Gf5d5] } 31. Kg2 Qxd5) 30... Rxc1 31. Qxb8+ Rc8 32. Qb7 Qg4 { [%csl Gf3,Gg2,Gh3] } 33. Kg2 Nf3 { [%cal Gf3h4] } 34. Rh1 { [%cal Gh1h4] } 34... Rc2 $19) 29. Qxa8+) 28... Kh7 { White has no move. } { [%csl Gc4][%cal Gd5e7] } (28... Rxc4 { [%csl Gc4] } 29. Ne7+ { [%cal Ge7f5,Ge7g8] }) (28... Kf8 { Was even more precise, but as it is, White resigned } { [%cal Gd5e7] }) 29. Ne7 Rxc4 (29... Qf3 { [%csl Gh1,Gc4] }) 30. Nxf5 Nd3+ { [%csl Gc1] } 31. Ke2 Nxc1+ 32. Rxc1 *


